==English==
===Etymology===
German [[Horst]] ‘heap’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hɔ:st/

===Noun===
'''horst'''
#{{geology}} an area of the earth's surface which is raised relative to surrounding land
#:*'''1968''': Your body is a '''horst''' and mine a graben, because horst is the opposite of graben. — Anthony Burgess, ''Enderby Outside''
